    "LMSs, on the other hand, can offer a wider range of online courses that are more inclusive than MOOCs and try to meet the needs of specific students.",
    "Students enrolled in LMS's programs or courses can communicate with each other and receive individualized attention from instructors.",
    "Therefore, in MOOCs, students need to encourage and motivate themselves to complete their courses, while in LMSs, students are attempt to complete the course but either fail or withdraw due to their lack of understanding or for other causes Bendou et al (2017); Mihaescu and Popescu (2021).",
    "While many studies have used publicly available datasets such as MOOCs as they include a considerable number of courses and students, the majority of studies have used private datasets from LMSs, as they contain more specific courses and student's receive specific attention.",
